    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "True. I just took a look and it seems like glob is being used in two places: `FilesWriter` and `nbconvertapp`. You could argue that it's redundant in `nbconvertapp` as well -- so probably if you wanted to remove the glob functionality from `FilesWriter` it should be removed from `nbconvertapp` too? Otherwise it seems weird that you would be able to do `c.NbConvertApp.notebooks = ['*.ipynb']` but not `c.FilesWriter.files = ['my_directory/*']`.\n"
