    "created_at": "2014-09-15T15:45:30Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-09-15T15:45:30Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "nbconvert already does globbing using `glob.glob` when it looks to find notebooks to convert. But right now, if you glob for notebooks in different diretories nbconvert doesn't really work well. I have a fix for that in nbgrader that I will port over. It makes it so that nbconvert does a `chdir` to the directory of a notebook before converting it. \n\nWith this in mind, @jhamrick what is the usage case you are trying to target with this particular fix?\n"
  },
